<FIRST>r a PM-CoffeemakerRecall     01-12 0139</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Coffeemaker Recall,0145</SECOND>
<HEAD>Coffeemaker Recalled; Can Overheat, Catch Fire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SHELTON, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Black &amp; Decker Inc. says it is voluntarily
recalling two space-saving coffeemakers because they can overheat
and catch fire.
   The recall applies to all Model PDC401 and Model PDC403
Spacemaker Plus Thermal Carafe Coffeemakers bought after July 1988.
   The coffeemakers, which ordinarily hang from underneath kitchen
cabinets, overheat when water does not flow properly from the
reservoir to the heating unit, Black &amp; Decker said.
   Company officials said Wednesday they are aware of ``a few
instances'' of such fires.
   Black &amp; Decker said customers who return the coffeemakers will
get a free substitute plus a full refund or a certificate for a
redesigned model, which is expected to be available in April.
   The toll-free number for instructions on how to return the
coffeemakers is 1-800-833-3396.
</TEXT>
