<HEAD>Palm Beach Town Council Votes on Parking Ban to Discourage Surfers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PALM BEACH, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Lawn mowing is banned on Sundays, noisy
tennis ball machines are outlawed in the mornings and hanging
laundry outside is strictly forbidden.
   So it's no surprise that surfers are unwelcome in this posh
seaside town.
   ``These are very undesirable people coming into town,'' said
resident Alan Beal.
