<FIRST>d a AM-BRF--PresidentialLimo     01-12 0173</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Presidential Limo,0176</SECOND>
<HEAD>Ford Delivers New Limo For President</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto DT3 of Jan. 12</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ford Motor Co. on Thursday delivered a new
presidential limousine to the Secret Service, just in time for the
new administration.
   The 22-foot modified 1989 Lincoln Town Car will first be used in
President-elect Bush's inaugural parade Jan. 20.
   ``It's an honor to help provide security for the president and to
be associated with the prestige of the office of the president of
the United States,'' Ford's Lincoln-Mercury General Manager Ross
Roberts said in a statement.
   The black limo is 44.7 inches longer and 6.1 inches taller than a
conventional Town Car. Its chassis was redesigned and a 7.5-liter
engine was used primarily because of increased weight from armor
plating and communications equipment.
   The weight of the car was not revealed for security reasons, Ford
spokesman J.F. ter Horst said. The hand-built car, a reassembled
Town Car from Ford's Wixom assembly plant, has separate air
conditioning and heating systems for the driver and passenger
compartments.
</TEXT>
