<FIRST>d a AM-BRF--AbortionProtesters     01-12 0141</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Abortion Protesters,0145</SECOND>
<HEAD>Charges Dropped Against Abortion Protesters</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BUFFALO, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A judge dismissed trespassing charges
Thursday against 125 abortion protesters arrested during a
demonstration outside an abortion clinic.
   City Judge Joseph Figliola said the police complaint forms lodged
Nov. 19, the day of the protest, and subsequent affidavits filed by
prosecutors are ``completely barren'' of proof that the protesters
knew they were on private property without permission or that they
were told to leave the clinic grounds.
   The judge said he found no evidence that would support efforts to
force the protesters to stand trial.
   The judge apparently left the door open for prosecutors either to
appeal his ruling or try to file new complaints.
   The 125 anti-abortion protesters had been cited for allegedly
trespassing on the grounds of a clinic operated by Dr. Parvis Taefi
of Buffalo.
</TEXT>
