<SECOND>AM-Liposuction Death,0233</SECOND>
<HEAD>Woman Gets House Arrest in Death of Friend</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHOENIX (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A medical assistant who tried to perform
liposuction but wound up killing her best friend instead was
sentenced Thursday to 45 days in jail and four years of intensive
probation.
   Stacy Lin Bickel, 25, of Tempe pleaded guilty in November to
negligent homicide in the death of Deborah Sue Tomazin, 24, of
Phoenix.
   She admitted giving Miss Tomazin an unintentionally lethal dose
of anesthetic while trying to prepare her for the medical procedure,
in which fatty cells are sucked from the body.
   The bungled attempt took place March 27 in the office of Miss
Bickel's former employer, Tempe plastic surgeon Richard Pavese.
   Maricopa County Superior Court Judge Lindsay Ellis also ordered
Miss Bickel to pay $5,500 in restitution to Miss Tomazin's family
and to perform 40 hours per week of community service indefinitely.
   A clerk for Ms. Ellis said intensive probation amounted to house
arrest, requiring written approval in advance of any
outside-the-residence activity.
   Miss Bickel will be able to work, the clerk said, but it was not
known if she had regained employment since she was fired.
   Detectives said Miss Tomazin, who died March 30, agreed to
undergo liposuction at the hands of her friend, who had assisted
Pavese in many operations and felt confident she could carry out the
procedure.
